### Slide 6: Business Model

**Purpose:** Show how you make money and unit economics

**What to Include:**
- Revenue model (how you charge)
- Pricing strategy
- Unit economics (CAC, LTV, ratio)
- Path to profitability
- Key assumptions

**Structure:**

```
Business Model: [Type]

Revenue Model:
[How you charge - subscription, transaction, etc.]

Pricing:
[Specific price points and rationale]

Unit Economics:
â€¢ CAC (Customer Acquisition Cost): $XX
â€¢ LTV (Lifetime Value): $XXX  
â€¢ LTV:CAC Ratio: X:1
â€¢ Payback Period: X months

Path to Profitability:
[When and how you become profitable]
```

**Example - Good:**

```
Freemium SaaS Model

Revenue Model:
â€¢ Free tier: Basic event discovery
â€¢ Premium ($4.99/month): Scholarship alerts, priority access
â€¢ Enterprise ($199/month): Whole-club admin tools

Target Mix: 15% premium conversion (industry standard: 10-15%)

Unit Economics:
â€¢ CAC: $12 (Instagram ads + referrals)
â€¢ LTV: $89 (avg. 18-month subscription @ $4.99/mo)
â€¢ LTV:CAC Ratio: 7.4:1 âœ… (target: >3:1)
â€¢ Payback Period: 2.4 months âœ… (target: <12 mo)

Profitability: Month 18 at 2,000 paying users
```

**Example - Bad:**

```
Business Model

We will charge users for premium features.

Some users will pay, some won't.

We will make money eventually.
```

**Why Bad Example Fails:**
- No specific pricing
- No unit economics
- No evidence or benchmarks
- No path to profitability

**Common Revenue Models:**

**SaaS/Subscription:**
- Monthly or annual recurring revenue
- Example: $9.99/month per user

**Freemium:**
- Free basic, paid premium features
- Example: 10-15% conversion rate

**Transaction Fee:**
- Percentage of each transaction
- Example: 3% of event ticket sales

**Marketplace:**
- Commission on matches/sales
- Example: 15% commission on tutoring bookings

**Enterprise/B2B:**
- Per-seat or per-organization pricing
- Example: $1,999/year for university license

**Connecting to Lab 9 Financial Model:**

Your Lab 9 deliverables directly inform this slide:
- âœ… Use your calculated CAC from financial model
- âœ… Use your calculated LTV from cohort analysis
- âœ… Reference your 12-month revenue projections
- âœ… Show your unit economics dashboard metrics

**Your Business Model Checklist:**
- [ ] Clear revenue model
- [ ] Specific pricing
- [ ] CAC calculated and realistic
- [ ] LTV calculated with rationale
- [ ] LTV:CAC ratio > 3:1
- [ ] Payback period < 12 months
- [ ] Path to profitability shown

