### Slide 9: Team

**Purpose:** Prove you're the right people to build this

**Key Message:** Investors invest in people first, ideas second

**What to Include:**
- Team member roles and relevant experience
- Domain expertise or unique insights
- Complementary skills
- Credibility indicators

**The Hacker-Hustler-Hipster Framework:**

Every team needs:
- **Hacker**: Technical builder (CTO)
- **Hustler**: Business driver (CEO)
- **Hipster**: Design/UX expert (CPO)

**Structure:**

```
The Team

[Photo of team - professional but approachable]

[Name 1] - CEO/Co-Founder
â€¢ [Relevant experience]
â€¢ [Domain expertise]
â€¢ [Why they're perfect for this role]

[Name 2] - CTO/Co-Founder  
â€¢ [Technical background]
â€¢ [Relevant projects]
â€¢ [Why they're perfect for this role]

[Name 3] - [Role]
â€¢ [Relevant experience]
â€¢ [Unique skill]
â€¢ [Why they're perfect for this role]

Why We're the Right Team:
[What makes this team uniquely qualified]
```

**Example - Good:**

```
The Team

Mariam Jikia - CEO
â€¢ KIU CS Senior, President of Career Club (200 members)
â€¢ Experienced the opportunity-loss problem firsthand
â€¢ Led 3 campus initiatives reaching 500+ students

Giorgi Beridze - CTO
â€¢ Built 2 mobile apps with 1,000+ downloads
â€¢ Won KIU Hackathon 2024
â€¢ Internship at TBC Bank (mobile team)

Nino Kapanadze - Head of Design
â€¢ UX Design Certificate, Interaction Design Foundation
â€¢ Designed interfaces for 2 campus organizations
â€¢ Conducted 15+ usability tests for course projects

Why We're the Right Team:
We live and breathe the KIU student experience. We're not 
outsiders trying to fix university lifeâ€”we're students building 
for ourselves and our peers.
```

**Example - Bad:**

```
The Team

We are four CS students.

We all know how to code.

We work well together.
```

**Why Bad Example Fails:**
- Generic descriptions
- No specific achievements
- No domain expertise highlighted
- Doesn't build credibility

**What if You Don't Have Much Experience?**

**Highlight:**
- âœ… Relevant coursework or projects
- âœ… Domain expertise (you ARE students, for student problems)
- âœ… Specific skills demonstrated in this course
- âœ… Personal connection to the problem
- âœ… Complementary skill sets

**Avoid:**
- âŒ Exaggerating experience
- âŒ Generic statements
- âŒ Focusing on weaknesses
- âŒ Apologizing for being students

**Your Team Checklist:**
- [ ] Each person has specific role
- [ ] Relevant experience highlighted
- [ ] Domain expertise or unique insights
- [ ] Complementary skills shown
- [ ] Why THIS team for THIS problem
- [ ] Professional but authentic

