## Checklist

### Pre-Design Checklist

Before you start designing, ensure you have:

**Content:**
- [ ] Problem validated with 15+ interviews
- [ ] Solution clearly articulated
- [ ] Product screenshots/demo ready
- [ ] Market size calculated (TAM/SAM/SOM)
- [ ] Business model with unit economics
- [ ] Traction metrics compiled
- [ ] Competitive analysis complete
- [ ] Team bios written
- [ ] Clear ask defined

**Materials:**
- [ ] High-res product screenshots
- [ ] Team photos (professional)
- [ ] Charts/graphs from Lab 9
- [ ] Customer quotes from interviews
- [ ] Logo/branding (if applicable)

### Design Checklist

Once you're designing:

**Structure:**
- [ ] Exactly 10 slides (no more, no less)
- [ ] Follows Guy Kawasaki framework
- [ ] Logical flow from problem to ask
- [ ] Clear transitions between slides

**Visual:**
- [ ] Consistent font throughout (30pt min)
- [ ] 2-3 color palette max
- [ ] High-quality images (no pixelation)
- [ ] Clean, uncluttered layouts
- [ ] Passes squint test

**Content:**
- [ ] No paragraphs (bullets only)
- [ ] Max 5 bullets per slide
- [ ] Max 7 words per bullet
- [ ] All numbers specific (not "many")
- [ ] All claims backed by evidence

**Polish:**
- [ ] Spell-checked
- [ ] Grammar-checked
- [ ] Consistent formatting
- [ ] Slide numbers included
- [ ] Team names/contact on final slide

### Pre-Presentation Checklist

Before Demo Day:

**Technical:**
- [ ] PDF format (not PPT - no compatibility issues)
- [ ] Tested on presentation computer
- [ ] Backup on USB drive
- [ ] Demo rehearsed 10+ times
- [ ] Demo video backup ready
- [ ] Internet connection not required (if possible)

**Delivery:**
- [ ] Pitch timed to 7 minutes
- [ ] Speaker roles assigned
- [ ] Transitions practiced
- [ ] Q&A prep done
- [ ] Emergency plan if demo fails

**Final Review:**
- [ ] Instructor feedback incorporated
- [ ] Peer feedback incorporated
- [ ] All typos fixed
- [ ] All numbers verified
- [ ] Contact information correct

---

## Final Tips

### The Week Before Demo Day

**Monday-Tuesday:**
- Finalize all content
- Get design feedback
- First full rehearsal

**Wednesday-Thursday:**
- Polish design
- Practice, practice, practice
- Record backup demo video

**Friday:**
- Final edits only (no major changes)
- Full dress rehearsal with timer
- Submit final deck

**Weekend:**
- Light practice (don't over-rehearse)
- Rest and prepare mentally
- Review Q&A prep

**Demo Day:**
- Arrive early
- Test technical setup
- Breathe and deliver with confidence

### Remember

> "The best pitch decks tell a story that leaves the audience wanting to know more. Your goal isn't to tell them everythingâ€”it's to make them care enough to ask."

**You've got this! ðŸš€**

